# Summary
This documentation outlines best practices for getting started with Amplitude Data, including starting with goals and metrics, maintaining simple naming conventions, properly identifying users, choosing between server-side and client-side event collection, using properties effectively, separating development and production environments, implementing QA analysis in CI/CD, and designating an owner for the tracking plan.

